comments: Kuminga (GSW) is established in front of Primo (SAS) when marginal body contact occurs on the shot attempt.
Green (GSW) establishes himself in a screening position in Jones' (SAS) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Poole (GSW) moves laterally into Primo's (SAS) path and affects his SQBR on the perimeter.
The ball is dislodged off Collins' (SAS) forearm last before going out of bounds. The Warriors are correctly awarded possession.

During the screen, Wieskamp (SAS) and Porter Jr. (GSW) engage and disengage, and the contact is marginal.  As he cuts to the perimeter, Porter Jr.'s (GSW) feet come together, causing him to lose his balance.
Landale (SAS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Collins (SAS) brings his right arm down from a vertical position and makes contact with Kuminga's (GSW) wrist, which affects his play at the basket.
Jones (SAS) slightly extends his arm to release from the marginal contact with Poole (GSW) as they come together at the end of the drive.
Green (GSW) maintains a legal guarding position by collapsing his forearm into his body and absorbing the contact during Jones' (SAS) driving shot attempt.
Primo (SAS) is late and trailing behind Poole (GSW) when he makes contact with his back/shoulder, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Collins (SAS) rests his hands on Iguodala's (GSW) body, without extending them, and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Wiggins (GSW) legally contests Landale's (SAS) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Collins (SAS) and Iguodala (GSW) engage and disengage, and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Jones' (SAS) hand brushes Poole's (GSW) arm, causing marginal contact to occur.

Replay review of the foul called on Jones (SAS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Jones (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position alongside Poole (GSW) as he slips on the perimeter.
During the inbound, Wieskamp (SAS) and Lee (GSW) mutually engage and disengage, and the contact is marginal.
Primo (SAS) commits a take foul on Poole (GSW).
During the inbound, Payton II (GSW) and Jones (SAS) engage and disengage, and the contact is marginal.
Green (GSW) legally contests Jones' (SAS) jump shot attempt.
